# MeldUI Package Registry Configuration
#
# MeldUI packages are published to GitHub Packages.
# To install @meldui packages, you need to configure npm to use GitHub Packages
# for the @meldui scope.
#
# Usage:
# 1. Copy this file to your project root or home directory:
#    cp .npmrc.example .npmrc
#    OR
#    cp .npmrc.example ~/.npmrc
#
# 2. If copying to home directory (~/.npmrc), uncomment the authToken line
#    and replace YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN with a personal access token
#
# 3. Create a GitHub Personal Access Token:
#    - Go to https://github.com/settings/tokens
#    - Click "Generate new token (classic)"
#    - Select scope: "read:packages"
#    - Copy the token
#
# 4. Replace YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN below with your token

# Configure @meldui packages to use GitHub Packages registry
@meldui:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com

# Uncomment and add your GitHub token if using ~/.npmrc (global config)
# //npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN

# Alternative: Use npm login instead of token
# Run: npm login --scope=@meldui --registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
